lled shifts in the next 48 hours alongside persistent 0% fill rates over 30 days across 5 sites is unusual. It is possible that shifts exist but are not surfacing correctly in the unfilled shift feed, meaning real coverage gaps may be going undetected.","likelihood":"medium","impact":"critical","affectedEntity":"All 5 Problematic Sites"},{"title":"Hyatt Hotel Operational Risk","description":"With 21 shifts at 0% fill over 30 days and no improvement trend, Hyatt Hotel faces significant risk of understaffing if these shifts are active and workers are not being successfully assigned.","likelihood":"high","impact":"critical","affectedEntity":"Hyatt Hotel","affectedEntityId":"c3339152-ff0d-41f9-b5cd-ed14c1721d7e"},{"title":"Shift Offer Pipeline Inefficiency","description":"A 33% acceptance rate on shift offers means 2 out of 3 offers did not result in a filled shift. If this trend continues at scale, fill rates will remain low even as more offers are sent.","likelihood":"medium","impact":"medium","affectedEntity":"Shift Offer System"}],"supportingEvidence":[{"metric":"Unfilled Shifts (Next 12h)","value":"0","context":"No shifts require immediate staffing action in the next 12 hours.","period":"Next 12 hours"},{"metric":"Unfilled Shifts (Next 24h)","value":"0","context":"No shifts require staffing action in the next 24 hours.","period":"Next 24 hours"},{"metric":"Unfilled Shifts (Next 48h)","value":"0","context":"No shifts require staffing action in the next 48 hours.","period":"Next 48 hours"},{"metric":"Hyatt Hotel Total Shifts (30d)","value":"21 shifts, 0 filled (0%)","context":"Largest volume of persistently unfilled shifts across all sites.","period":"30-day"},{"metric":"Shift Offer Acceptance Rate","value":"33% (1 of 3 offers accepted)","context":"Low acceptance rate may be limiting the ability to fill open positions.","period":"Current"},{"metric":"Total Problematic Sites","value":"5","context":"All 5 flagged sites have a 0% fill rate and an issue score of 60.","period":"Current"}],"recommendedActions":[{"title":"Verify Unfilled Shift Data Integrity","description":"Investigate why 5 sites show 0% fill rates over 30 days while the unfilled shift feed shows zero open shifts in the next 48 hours. Confirm whether shifts are being posted correctly and whether the data pipeline is functioning as expected. This discrepancy should be resolved before drawing further conclusions.","priority":"urgent","category":"Data Integrity"},{"title":"Prioritize Hyatt Hotel Staffing Review","description":"With 21 shifts at 0% fill over 30 days, conduct an immediate review of Hyatt Hotel's shift postings, worker pool availability, and offer history to determine why no shifts are being filled.","priority":"urgent","category":"Site Management"},{"title":"Investigate Low Shift Offer Acceptance Rate","description":"Review the 3 shift offers sent — identify which sites they were for, why 2 were not accepted, and whether offer timing, pay rates, or worker availability are contributing factors.","priority":"high","category":"Shift Offers"},{"title":"Expand Worker Pool for Problematic Sites","description":"For HOLIDAY INN VICTORIA, Holiday Inn Express, Best Western, Motel 6 Victoria, and Hyatt Hotel, review whether enough qualified workers are being invited to shifts. Consider broadening eligibility criteria or recruiting additional workers for these locations.","priority":"high","category":"Workforce Planning"},{"title":"Monitor Fill Rate Trends Weekly","description":"All 5 problematic sites show a 'stable' trend at 0% — meaning there is no improvement over time. Set up weekly review checkpoints to track whether interventions are having an effect.","priority":"medium","category":"Monitoring"}],"confidenceScore":0.72,"severityScore":0.75}	29637	2ad7862c-99f0-458e-ac1c-0b05af8da95a	2026-03-11 05:06:06.398519
