 attendance patterns. A single no-show or late arrival in the next period would represent a 100% incident rate for that worker, potentially triggering false alarms.","likelihood":"medium","impact":"medium","affectedEntity":"All Workers","affectedEntityId":null},{"title":"No Redundancy in Workforce Coverage","description":"With only 2 workers assigned to Skyward Building, any attendance failure — even a single no-show — would leave the site critically understaffed with no buffer capacity.","likelihood":"low","impact":"high","affectedEntity":"Skyward Building","affectedEntityId":"58eca480-c20b-45fc-986b-4569f192345d"},{"title":"Absence of Trend Visibility","description":"No reliability trend data exists, meaning early warning signals of worker disengagement or declining performance cannot currently be detected. Issues may only become visible after they have already escalated.","likelihood":"medium","impact":"medium","affectedEntity":"All Workers","affectedEntityId":null}],"supportingEvidence":[{"metric":"Average Reliability Score","value":"100 / 100","context":"Both workers scored perfectly across lateness, no-show, and cancellation sub-scores.","period":"30-day"},{"metric":"Total Shifts Analysed","value":"2 (1 per worker)","context":"Very low shift volume significantly limits the statistical confidence of reliability scores.","period":"30-day"},{"metric":"High Risk Worker Count","value":"0","context":"No workers are currently flagged as high risk.","period":"30-day"},{"metric":"Declining Workers","value":"0","context":"No workers show a declining reliability trend, though trend history is absent.","period":"30-day"},{"metric":"Total Incidents (Late + No-Show + Cancel)","value":"0","context":"Zero attendance incidents recorded across all workers and shifts in the period.","period":"30-day"}],"recommendedActions":[{"title":"Expand Workforce at Skyward Building","description":"With only 2 workers covering a single site, there is no resilience against absences. Recruit or assign at least 1-2 additional workers to Skyward Building to ensure coverage continuity if an attendance issue arises.","priority":"medium","category":"Workforce Planning"},{"title":"Increase Shift Volume to Build Reliable Baselines","description":"Reliability scores based on 1 shift per worker are not statistically meaningful. Aim to schedule workers for a minimum of 5-10 shifts before drawing conclusions about their reliability profile.","priority":"medium","category":"Data Quality"},{"title":"Enable Historical Trend Tracking","description":"Ensure the system is capturing shift-level attendance data over time so that reliability trends can be computed in future periods. Early trend detection is critical for proactive intervention.","priority":"high","category":"Monitoring & Reporting"},{"title":"Conduct Proactive Check-In with Both Workers","description":"While performance is currently perfect, a brief engagement check-in with Test Worker and Bergel Sarenas can help identify any early concerns, confirm availability for upcoming shifts, and reinforce positive attendance behaviour.","priority":"low","category":"Worker Engagement"}],"confidenceScore":0.45,"severityScore":0.05}	26752	2ad7862c-99f0-458e-ac1c-0b05af8da95a	2026-03-11 05:06:43.469956
3754f65d-b41d-4a20-a197-f32ef1255281	\N	client_risk	{"question":"What should I worry about today?","dataKeys":["siteRiskScores","siteCancellations","siteNoShows","gpsFailures","reliabilityTrends","sitesNeedingEscalation","clientActivity","generatedAt"]}	{"assistantType":"client_risk","summary":"Two sites require immediate attention today: Motel 6 Victoria has a 100% no-show rate (1/1 shifts) and Hyatt Hotel has a 23.8% no-show rate across a meaningful 21-shift volume. Additionally, 32 of 37 active sites have had zero shift activity recently, signaling a significant client engagement concern across the portfolio.","keyFindings":[{"title":"Motel 6 Victoria — 100% No-Show Rate","detail":"The single shift scheduled at Motel 6 Victoria resulted in a no-show, producing a 100% no-show rate and a risk score of 55 — the highest in the portfolio. While the volume is just 1 shift, a complete service failure at any site warrants immediate follow-up. The fill rate is also 0%, meaning the shift was never backfilled. This client may be at risk of churn if not addressed promptly.","category":"No-Show / Service Failure","severity":"high"},{"title":"Hyatt Hotel — Elevated No-Show Rate at Scale","detail":"Hyatt Hotel has a 23.8% no-show rate across 21 shifts — a statistically significant and operationally serious pattern. Nearly 1 in 4 shifts is experiencing a no-show, and the fill rate is 0%, indicating these gaps are not being recovered. With a risk score of 32.14, this is the second-highest risk site and the most concerning from a volume-weighted perspective. Chronic no-shows at a high-volume site can damage the client relationship and service reputation.","category":"No-Show / Service Reliability","severity":"high"},{"title":"Skyward Building — Reliability Score Dropped 50%","detail":"Skyward Building's reliability score declined from 100 to 50 between periods — a 50% drop. The site currently shows 0 shifts in the active period, suggesting it may have gone dormant after previously active service. This sharp decline warrants investigation into whether the client relationship has stalled or if scheduling has simply not resumed.","category":"Reliability Trend","severity":"medium"},{"title":"32 of 37 Sites Have No Recent Shift Activity","detail":"Only 5 of 37 active sites have had shifts in the recent period. The remaining 32 sites are marked active but show zero shifts, zero risk events, and zero engagement. This could indicate dormant client relationships, onboarding accounts that haven't launched, or data gaps. At this scale, it represents a significant portfolio utilization and revenue risk.","category":"Client Activity","severity":"medium"},{"title":"Fill Rate Is 0% Across All Active Sites","detail":"Every site with recorded shifts shows a 0% fill rate. This means no-shows and gaps are not being backfilled. Whether this reflects a platform configuration issue, lack of available workers, or a data reporting gap, it is a systemic concern that compounds the impact of no-shows at Motel 6 Victoria and Hyatt Hotel.","category":"Service Reliability","severity":"high"}],"risks":[{"title":"Client Churn at Motel 6 Victoria","description":"A 100% no-show rate on the only shift on record, with no backfill, means this client received zero service. If unaddressed, this is a high churn risk — especially for a smaller-volume client where a single failure represents the entire relationship.","likelihood":"high","impact":"high","affectedEntity":"Motel 6 Victoria","affectedEntityId":"22b8f3b6-debf-4f1b-a25f-5b11331a310f"},{"title":"Ongoing Service Degradation at Hyatt Hotel","description":"A sustained 23.8% no-show rate across 21 shifts with no fill recovery suggests a systemic worker reliability or scheduling problem at this site. Continued degradation could lead to formal complaints, contract review, or loss of the account.","likelihood":"high","impact":"high","affectedEntity":"Hyatt Hotel","affectedEntityId":"c3339152-ff0d-41f9-b5cd-ed14c1721d7e"},{"title"