hers may be quietly disengaging. This is a revenue and relationship risk that deserves a structured review — who's genuinely active, who's stalled, and who needs a check-in call.\n\n---\n\n## 🟡 Keep an Eye On\n\n### 6. Skyward Building Went Quiet\nThis was your only well-performing site — 100% fill rate, reliable workers. But shift activity has dropped to zero and their reliability score has fallen sharply. It may just be a scheduling gap, but it's worth a quick check to confirm the relationship is still on track.\n\n### 7. Your Attendance Data Is Too Thin to Trust\nOnly 2 workers have been tracked for reliability, each with just 1 shift. The numbers look perfect, but they don't mean much yet. Don't let a clean report create a false sense of security — you don't have enough data to draw real conclusions here.\n\n---\n\n## The One-Line Summary\n**Your core problem today is Hyatt Hotel and Motel 6 Victoria — one client got no service at all, and your largest active site has been broken for a month. Everything else flows from the same root cause: not enough workers in Victoria to fill the shifts you're selling.**	{"assistantsInvoked":["staffing","attendance","client_risk"],"overallSeverity":0.78,"metadata":{"totalDurationMs":62500,"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6"}}	2026-03-11 05:08:19.244523
